  "threadFeedback": [
    {
      "threadId": "PRRT_kwDORRAfU85yQcWH",
      "status": "accepted",
      "agentReasoning": "Duplicate `test-results/` entry on lines 48 and 50 of .gitignore is a trivial, clear cleanup. No risk of regression.",
      "resolvedAt": "2026-03-05T07:46:20.317Z"
    },
    {
      "threadId": "PRRT_kwDORRAfU85yQcWN",
      "status": "denied",
      "agentReasoning": "Story inline styles (`gap: 0.5rem`, `display: flex`) are demo scaffold HTML, not component theming. The `--hx-*` token rule applies to component source files (`.styles.ts`), not to wrapper divs in Storybook story render functions. Applying tokens to every layout helper in stories would make them harder to read and maintain with zero benefit to end users. The feedback misapplies the convention to the wrong layer.",
      "resolvedAt": "2026-03-05T07:46:20.317Z"
    },
    {
      "threadId": "PRRT_kwDORRAfU85yQcWV",
      "status": "denied",
      "agentReasoning": "The rem literal fallbacks (`var(--hx-size-6, 1.5rem)`) are intentional defensive programming. If consumer environments haven't loaded the token CSS, the component will still render at a sensible size. Removing the rem fallbacks would cause zero-size icons in environments where tokens are absent. This is a deliberate resilience pattern, not a violation — the \"no hardcoded values\" rule targets component property values, not the final fallback in a token cascade chain.",
      "resolvedAt": "2026-03-05T07:46:20.317Z"
    },
    {
      "threadId": "PRRT_kwDORRAfU85yQcWd",
      "status": "accepted",
      "agentReasoning": "Fixed `setTimeout(50)` waits are genuinely flaky in slower CI environments. Replacing them with a deterministic `waitForInlineSvg` helper that polls `updateComplete` and checks for actual DOM state is a real quality improvement. All 5 occurrences in the Sanitizer tests use the same pattern and can be updated uniformly.",
      "resolvedAt": "2026-03-05T07:46:20.317Z"
    },
    {
      "threadId": "PRRT_kwDORRAfU85yQcWi",
      "status": "accepted",
      "agentReasoning": "Biome flags `lint/suspicious/useIterableCallbackReturn` as an error on the expression-bodied forEach callback. The fix is trivial (add block braces) and eliminates a real lint error that would block `npm run verify`.",
      "resolvedAt": "2026-03-05T07:46:20.317Z"
    },
    {
      "threadId": "PRRT_kwDORRAfU85yQcWz",
      "status": "accepted",
      "agentReasoning": "The `test-results/.last-run.json` file is ephemeral Playwright output that was committed before being ignored. It records a failed local run state, pollutes diffs, and should not be in source control. The .gitignore already covers `test-results/` so only `git rm --cached` is needed.",
      "resolvedAt": "2026-03-05T07:46:20.317Z"
    }
  ],
  "remediationHistory": []
